  "prompt": "What universities does W&T offshore recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "W&T Offshore, Inc. is an independent oil and natural gas producer based in Houston, Texas. While specific recruitment details can vary from year to year, the company often recruits new graduates from universities with strong engineering, geosciences, and business programs. Here are some of the universities and majors that W&T Offshore might target:\n\n### Universities:\n1. **University of Texas at Austin**\n2. **Texas A&M University**\n3. **Louisiana State University**\n4. **University of Houston**\n5. **Colorado School of Mines**\n6. **University of Oklahoma**\n7. **Texas Tech University**\n\n### Majors:\n1. **Petroleum Engineering**\n2. **Chemical Engineering**\n3. **Mechanical Engineering**\n4. **Geological Sciences**\n5. **Geophysics**\n6. **Reservoir Engineering**\n7. **Business Administration/Finance (for roles in finance, accounting, and business development)**\n\n### Additional Information:\n- **Internships:** W&T Offshore often looks for interns from these universities, which can lead to full-time employment after graduation.\n- **Career Fairs:** They participate in career fairs at these universities to connect with potential candidates.\n- **Networking Events:** Professional and alumni networking events are another avenue they use to recruit new talent.\n\nTo get the most accurate and up-to-date information, I recommend checking W&T Offshore's careers page or contacting their HR department directly. Additionally, university career services offices may have specific details on company recruitment events and targeted majors.",
